.

Geographical distribution (
Fig. 75
). Genus with distribution restricted to the Americas.

Contemporary authors ( e.g.
Adlbauer 1993
;
Vitali 2008
) referring to North American Prioninae , frequently consider Mallodontini as a tribe of Prioninae . This concept is not formally accepted by any of the researchers who work with the New World fauna; most of which assign to Macrotomini all genera that would be included in Mallodontini .
